    "problemStatement": "You are given a tree consisting of NNN nodes and N\u22121N-1N\u22121 edges. The iii-th node has value AiA_iAi\u200b.\n\nLet d(x,y)d(x, y)d(x,y) denote the number of edges on the (unique) shortest path between xxx and yyy.\n\nFor each node u&nbsp;(1\u2264u\u2264N)u \\ (1 \\leq u \\leq N)u&nbsp;(1\u2264u\u2264N), compute the following quantity:\n\n\u2211i=1N\u230aAi2d(u,i)\u230b\\sum_{i=1}^N \\left \\lfloor \\frac{A_i}{2^{d(u, i)}} \\right\\rfloori=1\u2211N\u200b\u230a2d(u,i)Ai\u200b\u200b\u230bHere, \u230a&nbsp;\u230b\\left\\lfloor \\ \\right\\rfloor\u230a&nbsp;\u230b denotes the floor function.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of multiple lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer NNN \u2014 the number of nodes in the tree.\nThe next N\u22121N-1N\u22121 lines describe the edges. The iii-th of these N\u22121N-1N\u22121 lines contains two space-separated integers uiu_iui\u200b and viv_ivi\u200b, denoting an edge between uiu_iui\u200b and viv_ivi\u200b.\nThe next line contains NNN space separated integers A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1, A_2, \\ldots, A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line NNN space-separated integers, the iii-th of which denotes the answer for node iii.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641041 \\leq T \\leq 10^41\u2264T\u2264104",
